===============================================================================
EXAMPLE TOKENS MAPPED ONTO ROUTES (ILLUSTRATIVE)
===============================================================================

NOTE:
These examples are conceptual mappings to help humans. They do NOT claim
anything about current implementations or guarantees.

[GREEN] FIXED SUPPLY + BURN (no post-launch mint)
- Typical memecoins / simple governance tokens (fixed cap, burn optional)

[YELLOW] EMISSIONS TOKEN (rate-limited minter + pause)
- Typical staking reward tokens / incentive tokens / points-to-token systems

[RED] SECURE MINT (Proof-of-Reserve / collateral-gated)
- Reserve-backed stablecoins / wrapped assets / tokenized collateral claims

[RED] CROSS-CHAIN BURN-AND-MINT (canonical issuer)
- Native multi-chain issuer models (CCTP-style patterns conceptually)

===============================================================================
GLOBAL RULES ENFORCED BY THIS TREE
===============================================================================

• Backed token ⇒ [ROUTE:SECURE_MINT] is mandatory and has priority
• Emissions ⇒ [ROUTE:EMISSIONS] strict minter policy required
• Cross-chain ⇒ [ROUTE:CROSS_CHAIN] burn-and-mint preferred + reconciliation
• Any unbounded mint path ⇒ [BLACK] NO-GO
• Any invariant breach ⇒ pause + DAO escalation + evidence snapshot

